Articles.Content:
Hi.

I don't remember which mod this came with, one of the Kethane, Payload, or Satellite Packs from MMI surely.

I'm probably some sort of retarded, but I can't seem to get this thing to work. Every time I attach it to something the engine icon in the bottom right is blanked out. I've tried adding different fuel types to the vehicle in case that was the problem. But I can't figure it out. I'm pretty sure I saw someone using it in a video.

Anyone know what's up with it?
It is probably missing a plugin or something?
Looks like it's still using the old part syntax, if you are using a stock or already updated fuel tank it will not work.

Oh. So it's basically useless to me now? Should I just delete the part out of my folders. Or is there a fix for this sort of thing?

I'm not really good at any sort of scripting etc., but if I know what to change and where I can generally figure that stuff out.
Maybe somebody already has done an update to the MMI Satellite pack, search for it.

I've looked. The only place I have found to download it is where I already got it.

Which is here: http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/showthread.php/13692-Mechanical-Mouse-Industries-Kethane-Payload-Packs-Released!!!
